UMUAHIA – Abia State Governor, Dr. Okezie Ikpeazu, has disclosed that the government would put into use the N27billion loan facility it secured from the World Bank into total rebuilding of collapsed infra­structure in Aba, commercial nerve centre of the state. Governor Ikpeazu, who gave the reassurance while speaking at the 2021 Conven­tion & 20 Million Naira Visual Studio Fund Launch of The Presbyterian Church of Ni­geria, Aba Presbytery, held at the St. Andrew’s Presbyterian Church, First Aba Parish, as­sured Aba residents that the condition of Port Harcourt Road, Ngwa Road, Ohanku and roads around Ndiegoro, Aba, will soon change for the better, as his administration is committed to the total re­building of infrastructure in the town. He revealed that there is a plan to construct a five-and-a-half killometre tunnel to take storm water from Ndi­egoro to the Aba River so as permanently tackle the problem of flooding, which has been major challenge to those areas. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Dr. Ikpeazu promised that the state will witness great­er development in the days ahead and called for the sup­port and understanding of Abians.